hip%20Companies%20Urge%20India%20to%20Support%20Renewing%20E-commerce%20Moratorium%20at%20WTO%20Meeting%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22155858%2Fimage-1660.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Ministers%20from%20various%20nations%20will%20meet%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20on%20February%2026%20to%20discuss%20various%20trade-related%20issues%2C%20including%20a%20decision%20on%20whether%20to%20extend%20a%20moratorium%20in%20place%20since%201998%20on%20applying%20duties%20on%20electronic%20transmissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20moratorium%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erestricts%20countries%20from%20applying%20customs%20duties%20on%20electronic%20transmissions.%20As%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20since%201998%2C%20WTO%20members%20have%20periodically%20agreed%20to%20extend%20the%20moratorium%20on%20the%20imposition%20of%20customs%20duties%20on%20electronic%20transmissions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeveloping%20countries%20like%20India%20oppose%20this%20extension%2C%20fearing%20revenue%20loss.%20If%20no%20agreement%20is%20made%2C%20the%20moratorium%20would%20expire%20this%20year%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Semiconductor%20Council%2C%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20has%20said%20that%20if%20the%20moratorium%20ends%2C%20tariffs%20on%20digital%20commerce%20and%20chip%20design%20data%20transfers%20could%20spike%2C%20impacting%20the%20semiconductor%20industry.%20They%20have%20urged%20India%20to%20support%20a%20permanent%20ban%20on%20customs%20duties%20for%20cross-border%20digital%20transactions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Findia%2Findias-stance-data-transfers-wto-spooks-chip-giants-2024-02-23%2F%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Council%20has%20also%20warned%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20stance%20will%20stifle%20its%20own%20chip%20design%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Council%20represents%20chip%20giants%20like%20Intel%2C%20Qualcomm%20and%20Nvidia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fwhy-wto-is-not-an-appropriate-forum-for-negotiating-e-commerce-rules%5C%22%3EWhy%20WTO%20Is%20Not%20an%20Appropriate%20Forum%20for%20Negotiating%20E-commerce%20Rule%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%20BusinessLine%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Findia-unlikely-to-extend-moratorium-on-customs-duties-on-e-commerce%2Farticle67868118.ece%5C%22%3Equoted%20an%20official%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20saying%20that%20India%20is%20unlikely%20to%20extend%20the%20moratorium%20on%20the%20imposition%20of%20customs%20duties%20on%20electronic%20transmissions%20at%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%2013th%20Ministerial%20Conference%20(MC13)%2C%20as%20there%20is%20no%20consensus%20on%20its%20scope%20and%20it%20benefited%20mostly%20developed%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNew%20Delhi%20is%20not%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20further%20extension%20of%20the%20e-commerce%20moratorium.%20We%20are%20unlikely%20to%20do%20so%20at%20MC13.%20Those%20who%20demand%20the%20moratorium%20should%20tell%20us%20what%20its%20scope%20is%20and%20what%20all%20it%20covers.%20Only%20then%20we%20can%20decide%20if%20there%20is%20a%20need%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20official%20close%20to%20the%20negotiations%20told%20%3Ci%3E%3C%2Fi%3Ethe%20business%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20a%202017%20UNCTAD%20study%2C%20developing%20countries%20lose%20an%20estimated%20%2410%20billion%20every%20year%20in%20revenue%20because%20of%20the%20moratorium.%20For%20India%2C%20it%20could%20be%20over%20%24500%20million%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20argues%20that%20digital%20services%2C%20once%20physical%20goods%20like%20books%20and%20videos%2C%20should%20now%20be%20subject%20to%20duties%2C%20emphasising%20the%20revenue%20loss%20faced%20by%20developing%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Council%2C%20in%20its%20letter%2C%20urged%20India%20to%20work%20toward%20a%20WTO%20agreement%20to%20permanently%20prohibit%20countries%20from%20subjecting%20cross-border%20data%20and%20digital%20tools%20to%20customs%20duties%20and%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20support%20to%20renewing%20the%20moratorium%20will%20%E2%80%9Csend%20a%20strong%20signal%20to%20semiconductor%20companies%20that%20India%20is%20an%20investment%20friendly%20environment%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20group%20wrote%2C%20per%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2FIndustry%2F50-financial-assistance-to-firms-setting-up-semiconductor-manufacturing-unit-in-india-prime-minister-modi%2Farticle67130911.ece%5C%22%3Eis%20aiming%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20develop%20a%20strong%20semiconductor%20policy%20and%20become%20a%20global%20hub%20of%20semiconductor%20and%20chip-making%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202022%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Findia-approves-10-billion-plan-to-lure-semiconductor-and-display-makers%5C%22%3Elaunched%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20semiconductor%20policy%2C%20which%20includes%20a%20%2410%20billion%20incentive%20plan%20to%20attract%20semiconductor%20fabricators%20and%20display%20manufacturers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708753118000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22155858%2Fimage-1660.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fchip-companies-urge-india-to-support-renewing-e-commerce-moratorium-at-wto-meeting-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20World%20Semiconductor%20Council%2C%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20has%20said%20that%20if%20the%20moratorium%20ends%2C%20ta