t%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mark%20Zuckerberg%2C%20CEO%20of%20Meta%2C%20testifies%20during%20the%20Senate%20Judiciary%20Committee%20hearing%20titled%20%26quot%3BBig%20Tech%20and%20the%20Online%20Child%20Sexual%20Exploitation%20Crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20Dirksen%20building%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20January%2031%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d93d326080194819f9f3ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%2C%20CEO%20of%20Meta%2C%20testifies%20during%20the%20Senate%20Judiciary%20Committee%20hearing.%3Cp%3ETom%20Williams%2FCQ-Roll%20Call%2C%20Inc%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%20is%20trying%20to%20avoid%20personal%20liability%20in%20lawsuits%20over%20kids'%20social%20media%20addiction.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECorporate%20law%20typically%20shields%20executives%20from%20personal%20liability%2C%20though%20there%20are%20exceptions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20Zuckerberg%20is%20personally%20dropped%20from%20the%20lawsuits%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20dismiss%20cases%20against%20Meta.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20arguing%20he%20can't%20be%20held%20personally%20liable%20for%20accusations%20that%20his%20platforms%20have%20led%20to%20kids%20being%20addicted%20to%20social%20media%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he%20may%20have%20a%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg's%20legal%20team%20was%20in%20court%20in%20Oakland%2C%20California%2C%20this%20week%20over%20a%20string%20of%20lawsuits%20filed%20against%20Meta%20and%20him%20personally%20by%20parents%20and%20schools%20that%20allege%20his%20actions%20and%20Meta's%20have%20harmed%20children%20by%20causing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcure-screen-time-social-media-phone-addiction-app-one-sec-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%20addiction%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcbayarea.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Fmark-zuckerberg-social-media-addiction-allegations%2F3462354%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENBC%20Bay%20Area%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-instagram-facebook-meta-posting-era-vision-pro-quest-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20requested%20he%20personally%20be%20dropped%20from%20the%20two%20dozen%20lawsuits%2C%20which%20were%20filed%20by%20people%20from%20over%20a%20dozen%20states.%20A%20ruling%20in%20the%20billionaire's%20favor%20would%20excuse%20him%20from%20being%20held%20personally%20liable%20but%20would%20not%20dismiss%20the%20cases%20against%20Meta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuits%20claim%20that%20Zuckerberg's%20actions%20and%20inaction%20led%20to%20social%20media%20addiction%20and%20accused%20him%20of%20ignoring%20warnings%20that%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram%20were%20unsafe%20for%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%20records%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Zuckerberg's%20lawyers%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20fundamental%20principle%20that%20individuals%20cannot%20be%20held%20personally%20liable%20for%20the%20acts%20or%20omissions%20of%20a%20corporation%20based%20merely%20on%20their%20status%20as%20corporate%20executives%2C%20directors%2C%20or%20shareholders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20lawyers%20reiterated%20their%20arguments%20in%20court%20on%20Friday%2C%20saying%20there%20is%20a%20clear%20difference%20between%20what%20Zuckerberg%20as%20an%20individual%20is%20personally%20liable%20for%20and%20his%20role%20as%20CEO%2C%20NBC%20Bay%20Area%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20for%20Zuckerberg%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20corporate%20law%2C%20executives%20are%20typically%20shielded%20from%20personal%20liability%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-02-23%2Fzuckerberg-wants-no-personal-legal-blame-for-instagram-facebook-addiction%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20noted%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bcorporate%20veil%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20which%20generally%20refers%20to%20distinctions%20between%20a%20business%20and%20its%20owners%20%E2%80%94%20shields%20executives%20in%20most%20circumstances%2C%20although%20there%20are%20exceptions%2C%20according%20to%20an%20article%20from%20the%20law%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffederal-lawyer.com%2Fwhen-can-a-ceo-be-held-personally-liable%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOberheiden%20P.C.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20situations%20in%20which%20executives%20can%20face%20liability%20include%20criminal%20acts%20and%20intentional%20or%20grossly%20negligent%20noncompliance.%20They%20can%20also%20face%20liability%20in%20lawsuits%20filed%20by%20third%20parties%20against%20a%20CEO%2C%20Oberheiden%20P.C.%20wrote%2C%20noting%2C%20%26quot%3BIn%20these%20lawsuits%2C%20plaintiffs%20are%20not%20seeking%20to%20hold%20CEOs%20liable%20for%20corporate%20acts%20(or%20purportedly%20corporate%20acts)%2C%20but%20instead%20for%20acts%20undertaken%20by%20CEOs%20in%20their%20individual%20capacities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20when%20a%20civil%20lawsuit%20is%20filed%20against%20a%20CEO%20over%20an%20action%20they%20personally%20took.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiffs%20argued%20in%20court%20that%20Zuckerberg%20had%20a%20duty%20to%20share%20findings%20related%20to%20social%20media%20risks%20for%20kids%20publicly%2C%20but%20US%20District%20Judge%20Yvonne%20Gonzalez%20Rogers%20seemed%20skeptical%20of%20the%20argument%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20outlet%20reported%20the%20judge%20did%20suggest%20if%20it's%20determined%20Meta%20had%20a%20duty%20to%20disclose%20that%20information%2C%20then%20it's%20possible%20the%20CEO%20could%20be%20held%20liable%20for%20concealing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20knew%20the%20depth%20and%20breadth%20to%20which%20children%20were%20harmed%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%20by%20accessing%20and%20being%20addicted%20to%20the%20platforms%20that%20he%20is%20in%20charge%20of%20and%20did%20not%20take%20meaningful%20and%20significant%20action%20to%20remedy%20those%20harms%2C%20then%20he%20should%20be%20held%20personally%20liable%2C%26quot%3B%20Titania%20Jordan%20of%20Bark%20Technologies%2C%20an%20online%20safety%20and%20parental%20controls%20company%2C%20told%20NBC%20Bay%20Area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20if%20he%20can%20claim%20plausible%20deniability%20or%20if%20he%20was%20made%20aware%20of%20this%20and%20instructed%20his%20team%20to%20make%20it%20better%20or%20make%20it%20safer%20and%20they%20didn't%2C%20then%20that%20is%20on%20the%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Zuckerberg%20is%20deemed%20personally%20liable%2C%20it%20could%20have%20major%20implications%20for%20other%20lawsuits%20filed%20against%20CEOs%20of%20social%20media%20giants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-personal-liability-social-media-addiction-lawsuits-meta-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708745784000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d93dfa90413ab8e1d6a12a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-personal-liability-social-media-addiction-lawsuits-meta-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mark%20Zuckerberg%20says%20he%20can't%20be%20held%20personally%20liable%20in%20lawsuits%20alleging%20harm%20to%20kids%20with%20social%20media%20addiction%20just%20because%20he's%20CEO.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3