p%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EProduces%20less%20browning%2C%20takes%20a%20long%20time%20to%20preheat%2C%20cordierite%20is%20prone%20to%20cracking%20and%20staining%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Solido%2014x16%20Cordierite%20Pizza%20Stone%20makes%20delicious%20pizza%20that%20is%20moist%2C%20springy%2C%20and%20chewy.%20However%2C%20it%20doesn't%20produce%20quite%20the%20level%20of%20browning%20as%20the%20baking%20steel%20%E2%80%94%20the%20pizza%20was%20good%2C%20but%20still%20distinctly%20home-baked%20pizza%20not%20reminiscent%20of%20restaurant%20pizza.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDesign-wise%2C%20it's%20pretty%20basic%3A%20a%20rectangular%20slab%20of%20cordierite.%20However%2C%20unlike%20other%20cordierite%20stones%2C%20it%20has%20raised%20grooves%20along%20the%20bottom%20that%20lift%20it%20off%20the%20oven%20rack%20and%20make%20it%20much%20easier%20to%20grab%20and%20move%20around.%20While%20this%20is%20a%20minor%20design%20feature%2C%20it%20distinguished%20the%20Solido%20stone%20from%20other%20very%20similar%20stones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20rounded%20corners%20also%20fit%20better%20when%20I%20tried%20it%20on%20a%20charcoal%20grill.%20However%2C%20like%20all%20cordierite%20stones%2C%20it%20takes%20a%20long%20time%20to%20preheat%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20an%20inefficient%20option%20for%20grilling%20unless%20you%20want%20to%20waste%20a%20ton%20of%20propane%20or%20charcoal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20great%20stone%20if%20you%20loathe%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20unitasker%20%E2%80%94%20it%20made%20great%20oven%20pizza%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20excellent%20bread.%20It%20was%20also%20simple%20to%20clean%2C%20though%20it%20retained%20stains%20like%20all%20cordierite%20stones%20are%20prone%20to%20do.%20Cordierite%20can%20crack%20or%20break%20if%20not%20cared%20for%20properly%3B%20we%20don't%20expect%20this%20stone%20is%20any%20different%2C%20though%20we%20didn't%20see%20any%20cracking%20during%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20steel%3A%20The%20Original%20Baking%20Steel%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Baking%20Steel%20slide%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63a4afdf7877e10018fd6087%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterial%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20steel%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESize%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2014-inch%20by%2016-inch%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EExcellent%20thermal%20conductivity%20for%20superior%20pizza%2C%20preheats%20faster%20than%20cordierite%20stones%2C%20easy%20to%20clean%2C%20practically%20indestructible%2C%20doesn't%20show%20wear%20like%20cordierite%20stones%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHeavy%20to%20lift%2C%20gets%20too%20hot%20for%20baking%20bread%20or%20cooking%20on%20the%20grill%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20traditional%20pizza%20stones%2C%20which%20are%20made%20from%20ceramic%20or%20cordierite%20stone%2C%20the%20Baking%20Steel%20is%20(as%20the%20name%20suggests)%20made%20of%20steel%2C%20which%20transfers%20heat%20much%20faster.%20All%20materials%20have%20different%20thermal%20conductivity%2C%20meaning%20they%20hold%20and%20transfer%20heat%20differently.%20That's%20why%2C%20for%20example%2C%20it%20hurts%20to%20touch%20a%20hot%20oven%20rack%2C%20but%20only%20feels%20warm%20when%20you%20hold%20your%20hand%20in%20the%20oven%20air.%20When%20heated%20to%20500%20F%2C%20the%20Baking%20Steel%20behaves%20the%20same%20way%20as%20the%20surface%20of%20a%20traditional%20900%20F%20brick%20oven.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Baking%20Steel%20consistently%20made%20the%20most%20well-browned%2C%20bubbly%20pizzas%2C%20with%20great%20speckling%20across%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20crust.%20This%20not%20only%20made%20for%20pizza%20with%20a%20better%20texture%2C%20but%20also%20a%20more%20robust%20flavor%2C%20since%20those%20browned%20bits%20offer%20much%20more%20flavor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20properties%20that%20make%20the%20Baking%20Steel%20great%20for%20pizza%20make%20it%20a%20bad%20choice%20for%20bread%2C%20which%20needs%20slower%2C%20more%20consistent%20heat%20to%20bake%20properly.%20In%20testing%2C%20the%20Baking%20Steel%20burned%20the%20bottoms%20of%20my%20loaves.%20Steel%20also%20isn't%20a%20good%20choice%20for%20making%20pizza%20on%20the%20grill%2C%20where%20the%20temperatures%20exceed%20700%20F%20and%20the%20exceptional%20heat%20transfer%20from%20the%20steel%20becomes%20overkill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20steel%20is%20well-sized%20for%20pizzas%20that%20are%20large%20or%20aren't%20perfectly%20round.%20The%20slick%2C%20seasoned%20surface%20cleaned%20up%20easier%20than%20other%20stones%2C%20and%20while%20this%20is%20minor%2C%20I%20liked%20that%20the%20dark%20color%20didn't%20show%20wear%20the%20way%20ceramic%20and%20cordierite%20stones%20do.%20Since%20it's%20made%20from%20steel%2C%20it's%20also%20basically%20indestructible%20and%20thus%20much%20more%20durable%20than%20stone.%20If%20you're%20really%20serious%20about%20pizza%20quality%2C%20the%20Baking%20Steel%20is%20absolutely%20the%20best%20all-around%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Foriginal-baking-steel-vs-dough-joe-samurai%5C%22%3Efull%20review%20on%20how%20The%20Baking%20Steel%20compares%20to%20other%20pizza%20steels%20like%20the%20Dough-Joe%3C%2Fa%3E%20here.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20for%20the%20grill%3A%20Lodge%2015%20Inch%20Seasoned%20Cast%20Iron%20Pizza%20Pan%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lodge%20pan%20slide%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63a4afc97877e10018fd6074%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterial%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecast%20iron%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESize%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E15-inch%20diameter%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EGood%20thermal%20conductivity%20for%20well-browned%20pizzas%2C%20cleans%20up%20easily%2C%20doesn't%20show%20stains%2C%20circular%20shape%20fits%20well%20on%20round%20grill%2C%20handles%20make%20moving%20easy%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Difficult%20to%20slide%20a%20pizza%20onto%20its%20circular%20shape%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20you%20can%20make%20pizza%20directly%20on%20your%20grill's%20grates%20(in%20fact%2C%20this%20is%20the%20method%20Janjigian%20recommends%20if%20you're%20interested%20in%20grilled%20pizza)%2C%20a%20stone%20makes%20the%20process%20less%20daunting%20and%20potentially%20less%20messy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Lodge%2015%20Inch%20Seasoned%20Cast%20Iron%20Pizza%20Pan%20is%20well-suited%20to%20cooking%20on%20the%20grill%3B%20it%20offers%20a%20happy%20medium%20between%20steel%20and%20stone%20in%20how%20quickly%20it%20heats%20up%20and%20how%20fast%20it%20transfers%20heat%20to%20your%20pizza.%20In%20testing%2C%20the%20Lodge%20pan%20was%20ready%20to%20go%20after%20about%20a%20half-hour%20of%20preheating%20on%20my%20gas%20grill%2C%20and%20it%20cooked%20a%20beautifully%20baked%20pie%20with%20good%20spotting%20on%20the%20top%20and%20excellent%20browning%20on%20the%20bottom.%20The%20built-in%20handles%20made%20it%20easy%20to%20transfer%20the%20stone%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20grill%2C%20and%20it%20cleans%20up%20easily%20with%20just%20a%20sponge%20and%20some%20water.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrilling%20was%20also%20the%20only%20situation%20where%20I%20found%20the%20circular%20stone%20to%20have%20an%20advantage%20over%20rectangular%20stones%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-pizza-stone%23how-to-choose-a-pizza-stone-6%5C%22%3Eyou%20can%20read%20more%20about%20circular%20versus%20rectangular%20stones%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20the%20rectangular%20stones%20fit%20fine%20on%20my%20gas%20grill%2C%20some%20didn't%20fit%20at%20all%20on%20my%20small%20kettle%20charcoal%20grill.%20The%20round%20stone%20fit%20nicely%20in%20both%20the%20gas%20and%20charcoal%20grill%20and%20left%20plenty%20of%20room%20for%20air%20circulation.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stone%20isn't%20just%20for%20grilling%20though%3B%20it%20made%20excellent%20pizza%20in%20my%20oven%2C%20but%20I%20found%20its%20circular%20shape%20was%20less%20forgiving%20than%20rectangular%20stones.%20If%20I%20was%20off-center%20by%20just%20a%20bit%20when%20sliding%20the%20pizza%20off%20the%20peel%2C%20the%20dough%20hung%20off%20the%20edge%20and%20made%20a%20mess%20in%20my%20oven.%20This%20stone%20is%20a%20great%20option%20if%20you're%20dabbling%20in%20the%20world%20of%20grilled%20pizza%2C%20but%20most%20other%20users%20will%20get%20better%20benefits%20from%20one%20of%20our%20other%20rectangular%20picks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20a%20pizza%20stone%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Original%20Baking%20Steel%20and%20the%20Solido%20Cordierite%20Pizza%20Stone%20staged%20next%20to%20each%20other%20for%20comparison%2C%20two%20of%20the%20best%20pizza%20stones%20of%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5faaf3da1df1d5001821a017%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20considerations%20to%20think%20about%20when%20looking%20for%20a%20pizza%20stone%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPizza%20stone%20vs%20pizza%20steel%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20looked%20at%20stones%20made%20from%20steel%2C%20ceramic%20or%20cordierite%20stone%2C%20and%20cast%20iron%2C%20all%20of%20which%20have%20different%20thermal%20properties%2C%20and%20thus%2C%20different%20uses.%20Of%20these%2C%20steel%20absorbs%20and%20transfers%20heat%20the%20fastest%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20ideal%20for%20pizza%20in%20the%20home%20oven.%20If%20you're%20serious%20about%20good%20home%20pizza%2C%20we%20recommend%20opting%20for%20a%20pizza%20steel.%20Ceramic%20and%20cordierite%20stones%20make%20decent%20pizza%20but%20have%20less%20thermal%20mass%20than%20steel%2C%20so%20the%20crust%20tends%20to%20be%20paler%20and%20less%20developed.%20However%2C%20ceramic%20is%20a%20great%20choice%20if%20you%20plan%20on%20using%20your%20stone%20to%20bake%20bread%20since%20other%20materials%20tend%20to%20burn%20loaves.%20If%20you%20hate%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20unitasker%20and%20have%20a%20robust%20baking%20repertoire%2C%20a%20cordierite%20stone%20will%20absolutely%20do%20the%20trick.%20Finally%2C%20cast%20iron%20offers%20a%20happy%20medium%20between%20steel%20and%20ceramic%20in%20terms%20of%20heat%20conductivity.%20However%2C%20we%20have%20yet%20to%20find%20a%20rectangular%20cast%20iron%20stone%2C%20only%20circular%20pans%2C%20which%20are%20trickier%20to%20use.%20We%20think%20circular%20cast%20iron%20pizza%20stones%20are%20a%20good%20option%20if%20you're%20interested%20in%20grilled%20pizza%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20have%20a%20round%20grill.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShape%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOne%20might%20think%20that%20since%20pizza%20is%20round%2C%20a%20pizza%20stone%20should%20be%20too.%20But%20you'll%20get%20much%20better%20pizza%20out%20of%20a%20rectangular%20stone.%20Rectangular%20stones%20are%20often%20larger%2C%20so%20they%20hold%20more%20heat%2C%20which%20can%20make%20a%20pizza%20with%20better%20browning.%20Janjigian%20also%20thinks%20rectangular%20stones%20are%20more%20versatile%20for%20baking%20bread%20and%20other%20items%20that%20aren't%20perfectly%20round.%20The%20only%20time%20we%20see%20a%20round%20stone%20having%20an%20advantage%20is%20for%20grilling%2C%20since%20rectangular%20stones%20often%20don't%20fit%2C%20especially%20on%20circular%20grills.%20For%20almost%20all%20uses%2C%20rectangular%20is%20the%20way%20to%20go.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESize%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20my%20stone%20to%20be%20as%20big%20as%20my%20oven%20rack%2C%20minus%20some%20space%20for%20airflow%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Janjigian.%20A%20larger%20stone%20not%20only%20holds%20more%20heat%20but%20provides%20plenty%20of%20real%20estate%20for%20larger%20pies%20and%20long%20baked%20goods%20like%20baguettes.%20We%20found%20a%20stone%20that%20is%20about%2016%20inches%20by%2014%20inches%20to%20be%20the%20ideal%20size%20for%20most%20home%20ovens.%20For%20ceramic%20and%20cordierite%20stones%2C%20thicker%20is%20also%20better%2C%20says%20Janjigian%2C%20because%20thicker%20stones%20are%20less%20prone%20to%20cracking.%20Our%20favorite%20ceramic%20stone%20measures%20%C2%BE%20inch%20thick%2C%20and%20we%20found%20this%20size%20to%20be%20a%20good%20compromise%20between%20durability%20and%20maneuverability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeight%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhile%20lighter%20stones%20may%20be%20easier%20to%20transport%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20oven%2C%20Janjigian%20said%20that%20heavier%20stones%20will%20produce%20better%20pizza.%20%26quot%3BThe%20lighter%20it%20is%2C%20the%20less%20mass%20it%20has%2C%20and%20the%20less%20it%20can%20heat%20the%20pie%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20A%20heavier%20stone%20will%20hold%20a%20lot%20of%20heat%2C%20and%20make%20a%20well-browned%20pizza.%20Pizza%20stones%20usually%20weigh%20about%20nine%20pounds%2C%20but%20most%20of%20our%20top%20picks%20are%2013%20to%2016%20pounds%20because%20they're%20thicker%20or%20made%20with%20heavier%20material%20like%20steel%20or%20cast%20iron.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Pizza%20stones%20are%20basically%20just%20slabs%20of%20material%20so%20be%20wary%20of%20any%20stone%20priced%20significantly%20more%20or%20less%20than%20competitors%20made%20from%20the%20same%20material.%20Expect%20to%20pay%20about%20%2440%20to%20%2460%20for%20a%20ceramic%20or%20cast%20iron%20stone%20and%20%2470%20to%20%2490%20for%20a%20steel%20one.%20You%20won't%20get%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20performance%20from%20something%20priced%20higher.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVersatility%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhile%20pizza%20stones%20excel%20at%20making%20pizza%2C%20they're%20not%20unitaskers%3A%20they're%20also%20great%20for%20baking%20bread%2C%20searing%20steak%20or%20vegetables%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fhow-to-reheat-pizza%5C%22%3Ereheating%20leftovers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20found%20that%20large%2C%20rectangular%20stones%20made%20from%20ceramic%20or%20cordierite%20offered%20the%20most%20versatility%20for%20making%20more%20than%20just%20pizza.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20test%20pizza%20stones%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20left%20hand%20holding%20a%20slice%20of%20pepperoni%20pizza%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5faaf2951df1d5001821a009%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20interviewing%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwordloaf.substack.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Janjigian%3C%2Fa%3E%20(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fwordloaf%2F%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%40wordloaf%3C%2Fa%3E)%2Ca%20pizza%20expert%2C%20we%20put%20each%20pizza%20stone%20through%20a%20series%20of%20tests%20to%20judge%20how%20well%20they%20made%20pizza%2C%20and%20how%20easy%20they%20were%20to%20move%2C%20use%2C%20and%20clean.%20Here's%20how%20we%20tested%20and%20rated%20pizza%20stones%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShape%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20researched%20dozens%20of%20stones%2C%20but%20after%20conferring%20with%20Janjigian%2C%20focused%20on%20rectangular%20stones%20when%20I%20could%20because%20the%20shape%20is%20more%20versatile%20and%20easy%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20it%20made%20pizza%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20preheated%20each%20stone%20in%20a%20500-degree%20oven%20for%20two%20hours%20and%20then%20used%20it%20to%20make%20three%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seriouseats.com%2Fnew-york-style-pizza%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethin-crust%20pizzas%20using%20a%20recipe%20from%20Serious%20Eats%2C%20a%20website%20known%20for%20its%20science-based%2C%20well-tested%20recipes.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20several%20weeks%2C%20we%20adjusted%20cook%20time%2C%20oven%20temperature%2C%20and%20stone%20position%20in%20between%20pizzas%20in%20pursuit%20of%20the%20best%20results.%20A%20good%20pizza%20should%20have%20a%20well-browned%2C%20bubbly%20crust%20that%20is%20crisp%20on%20the%20outside%20and%20moist%20and%20chewy%20on%20the%20inside%3B%20cheese%20should%20be%20fully%20melted%20in%20the%20time%20it%20takes%20to%20cook%20the%20crust.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20both%20sampled%20each%20finished%20pizza%20for%20flavor%20and%20texture.%20I%20only%20tested%20the%20cast-iron%20pan%20on%20a%20charcoal%20grill%20because%20its%20size%2C%20shape%2C%20and%20material%20were%20best%20suited%20for%20that%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20it%20made%20bread%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMany%20people%20bake%20bread%20with%20their%20pizza%20stones%2C%20so%20I%20used%20each%20to%20make%20an%20easy%20recipe%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kingarthurbaking.com%2Frecipes%2Fno-knead-crusty-white-bread-recipe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrusty%20white%20bread%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20King%20Arthur%2C%20a%20respected%20flour%20company%20where%20Janjigian%20teaches%20baking%20classes.%20I%20looked%20for%20loaves%20that%20were%20well-baked%20inside%20and%20browned%20(but%20not%20burnt)%20on%20the%20bottom.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEase%20of%20Use%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20I%20frequently%20moved%20the%20stones%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20oven%20using%20oven%20mitts%2C%20and%20with%20my%20bare%20hands%20when%20the%20stones%20had%20cooled%20down%2C%20noting%20how%20easy%20and%20comfortable%20they%20were%20to%20move.%20After%20each%20use%2C%20I%20cleaned%20the%20stone%20according%20to%20manufacturer%20instructions%2C%20evaluating%20how%20easily%20they%20cleaned%20up%20and%20noting%20their%20appearance%20after%20use%20and%20cleaning.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDurability%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20didn't%20intentionally%20drop%20any%20stones%20during%20testing%2C%20as%20I%20know%20that%20cordierite%20in%20particular%20is%20prone%20to%20cracking%20and%20breaking%2C%20having%20broken%20a%20few%20of%20these%20stones%20in%20the%20past.%20Instead%2C%20I%20consulted%20with%20an%20expert%20and%20did%20my%20own%20research%20about%20the%20durability%20of%20different%20materials.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPizza%20stone%20FAQs%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20three%20best%20pizza%20stones%20of%202022%20staged%20next%20to%20each%20other%20displaying%20some%20wear%20and%20tear.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5faaf4351df1d5001821a018%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3EDoes%20a%20pizza%20stone%20make%20a%20difference%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20pizza%20stone%20can%20help%20you%20make%20restaurant-quality%20pizza%20at%20home.%20Pizza%20joints%20use%20commercial%20or%20wood-fired%20ovens%20that%20can%20reach%20900%2B%20F%2C%20creating%20the%20well-browned%20crust%20you%20expect%20from%20a%20restaurant%20pie.%20Home%20ovens%20don't%20get%20that%20hot%2C%20so%20a%20pizza%20stone%20recreates%20some%20of%20the%20restaurant%20experience%20by%20providing%20a%20super%20hot%20surface%20to%20cook%20the%20pizza%2C%20resulting%20in%20better%20browning%20and%20bubbling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20long%20should%20you%20preheat%20a%20pizza%20stone%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20the%20benefits%20of%20using%20a%20pizza%20stone%2C%20you%20absolutely%20must%20preheat%20it.%20Put%20your%20stone%20in%20the%20cold%20oven%20and%20preheat%20both%20stone%20and%20oven%20together%20for%20one%20to%20two%20hours.%20This%20step%20is%20essential%20for%20achieving%20a%20well-browned%20pizza.%20Without%20preheating%2C%20the%20results%20won't%20be%20much%20different%20than%20what%20you%20get%20from%20using%20a%20pizza%20pan%20or%20baking%20sheet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ECan%20I%20cook%20frozen%20pizza%20on%20my%20pizza%20stone%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThermal%20shock%20from%20placing%20frozen%20items%20on%20a%20hot%20stone%20can%20cause%20your%20stone%20to%20crack.%20Most%20frozen%20pizzas%20are%20parbaked%20at%20the%20factory%20and%20heating%20them%20simply%20involves%20warming%20the%20crust%20and%20melting%20the%20cheese.%20You%20likely%20won't%20see%20a%20marked%20difference%20if%20you're%20using%20a%20stone%20to%20cook%20a%20frozen%20pizza.%20If%20you%20do%20want%20to%20try%2C%20thaw%20your%20frozen%20pizza%20before%20placing%20it%20on%20the%20stone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhy%20is%20my%20pizza%20stone%20discolored%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20pizza%20stones%2C%20especially%20light-colored%20cordeirite%20and%20ceramic%20stones%2C%20are%20prone%20to%20discoloration%20with%20use.%20This%20discoloration%20happens%20when%20moisture%20and%20fat%20in%20the%20pizza%20ingredients%20(dough%2C%20sauce%2C%20cheese%2C%20etc.)%20interact%20with%20the%20stone%20material%20in%20the%20high%20temperatures%20of%20the%20oven.%20This%20discoloration%20does%20not%20negatively%20impact%20cooking%2C%20and%20over%20time%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20patina%20that%20will%20make%20your%20stone%20more%20nonstick%20as%20oils%20bond%20to%20the%20surface%20and%20form%20a%20natural%20protective%20coating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPizza%20stone%20tips%20and%20tricks%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Solido%20Cordierite%20Pizza%20Stone%20in%20Styrofoam%20packing%20with%20directions%20on%20top%2C%20one%20of%20the%20best%20baking%20stones%20of%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5faaf1eb1df1d5001821a004%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20Savoie%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20ever%20tried%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fhomemade-pizza%5C%22%3Emaking%20pizza%20in%20your%20home%20oven%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20any%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-pizza-making-tools%5C%22%3Especial%20pizza%20equipment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you've%20probably%20found%20the%20results%20pale%20and%20doughy%20compared%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Ftypes-of-pizza%5C%22%3Ewhat%20you%20get%20from%20your%20favorite%20pizza%20joint%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Home%20ovens%20max%20out%20at%20around%20550%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20unlike%20commercial%20or%20wood-fired%20pizza%20ovens%20that%20can%20reach%20900%2B%20degrees.%20Making%20great%20pizza%20at%20home%20takes%20practice.%20Here%20are%20some%20tips%20and%20tricks%20I've%20learned%20over%20a%20decade%20of%20working%20in%20professional%20kitchens%20to%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20your%20pizza%20stone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhen%20and%20how%20to%20season%20your%20stone%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20stones%20must%20be%20%26quot%3Bseasoned%26quot%3B%20before%20or%20between%20uses.%20Seasoning%20involves%20heating%20your%20stone%20without%20anything%20on%20it%20(except%20for%20maybe%20a%20light%20coat%20of%20oil).%20This%20practice%20helps%20expel%20any%20moisture%20from%20the%20stone%20that%20can%20cause%20cracking%20and%20make%20the%20surface%20more%20nonstick.%20Read%20the%20instructions%20included%20with%20your%20stone%20to%20determine%20if%20your%20stone%20should%20be%20seasoned%20and%20how%20to%20do%20it.%20Note%20that%20seasoning%20differs%20from%20pre-heating%3B%20we%20always%20recommend%20pre-heating%20your%20stone%20for%20at%20least%2030%20minutes%20(ideally%20several%20hours)%20before%20each%20use%20for%20best%20results.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20to%20clean%20a%20pizza%20stone%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20clean%20all%20types%20of%20pizza%20stones%20gently%20and%20without%20soap%20when%20you%20can%3B%20cordierite%20is%20very%20porous%2C%20and%20that%20soapy%20flavor%20can%20soak%20into%20the%20stone%20and%20impact%20the%20flavor%20of%20your%20pizza.%20Steel%20and%20cast%20iron%20should%20be%20cleaned%20lightly%20to%20not%20disturb%20the%20built-up%20seasoning.%20You%20can%20read%20more%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fhow-to-clean-a-pizza-stone%5C%22%3Ehow%20to%20clean%20a%20pizza%20stone%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20our%20guide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EPreventing%20your%20pizza%20stone%20from%20cracking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20%26quot%3Bstone%2C%26quot%3B%20cordierite%20pizza%20stones%20are%20relatively%20delicate.%20A%20common%20cause%20of%20cracking%20is%20thermal%20shock%2C%20which%20is%20when%20the%20stone%20is%20rapidly%20exposed%20to%20a%20drastically%20different%20temperature.%20You%20should%20never%20put%20a%20room%20temperature%20stone%20in%20a%20hot%20oven%3B%20always%20put%20the%20stone%20in%20a%20cold%20oven%20and%20allow%20it%20to%20preheat.%20Similarly%2C%20avoid%20putting%20frozen%20food%20onto%20a%20blazing%20hot%20stone%20(yes%2C%20that%20includes%20frozen%20pizza)%20and%20let%20the%20stone%20cool%20completely%20in%20the%20oven%20before%20removing%20or%20washing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStones%20can%20also%20crack%20from%20too%20much%20moisture.%20Give%20your%20stone%20time%20to%20dry%20after%20washing%20it%2C%20otherwise%20water%20in%20the%20stone%20and%20cause%20a%20build-up%20of%20steam%20the%20next%20time%20you%20heat%20the%20stone%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20crack.%20Finally%2C%20stones%20can%20crack%20from%20even%20minor%20drops%3B%20treat%20your%20stone%20as%20gently%20as%20you%20would%20a%20piece%20of%20pottery%20when%20handling%20or%20moving%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECast%20iron%20and%20steel%20stones%20should%20never%20crack%2C%20as%20both%20are%20extremely%20durable%20materials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20useful%20tools%20for%20making%20pizza%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20find%20the%20process%20making%20pizza%20much%20easier%20with%20the%20right%20tools.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-pizza-peel%5C%22%3Epizza%20peel%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20paddle-like%20tool%20to%20shuttle%20your%20pizza%20on%20and%20off%20the%20blazing%20hot%20stone.%20It%20makes%20the%20process%20significantly%20safer%2C%20cleaner%2C%20and%20less%20daunting.%20If%20you%20are%20using%20a%20pizza%20peel%2C%20your%20best%20bet%20is%20to%20make%20and%20top%20the%20pizza%20right%20on%20the%20peel.%20Also%20remember%20that%20pizza%20stones%20get%20really%20hot%3B%20you'll%20want%20a%20good%20pair%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-oven-mitts%5C%22%3Eoven%20mitts%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-bbq-gloves%5C%22%3Egrill%20gloves%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20protect%20your%20hands%20when%20you%20transfer%20pizza%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20oven.%20You%20may%20also%20want%20a%20dedicated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-pizza-cutter%5C%22%3Epizza%20cutter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20solid%20pair%20of%20tongs%20for%20rotating%20the%20pizza%20in%20the%20oven.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20