rought%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20British%20colonial%20government%20against%20the%20farmers%20of%20Punjab%20in%201907.%20The%20Punjab%20Land%20Colonisation%20Bill%20of%201906%20introduced%20inheritance%20by%20primogeniture%2C%20threatening%20that%20the%20lands%20of%20farmers%20would%20be%20snatched.%20The%20Bari%20Doab%20Canal%20Act%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsida.org.pk%2Fdownload%2Ftransition%2FE%2520Abiana%2520Report%2520Lahore%2520301122.pdf%5C%22%3Eincreased%3C%2Fa%3E%20water%20rates%20and%20revenue%20rates%20by%2025%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20March%20and%20May%201907%2C%20a%20number%20of%20meetings%20were%20held%20in%20different%20cities%20of%20Punjab%20to%20oppose%20the%20three%20laws%2C%20described%20as%20%E2%80%98black%20laws%E2%80%99%20by%20farmers.%20On%20March%2022%20of%20that%20year%2C%20Lala%20Banke%20Dayal%2C%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3EJhang%20Syal%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20recited%20his%20now-classic%20poem%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EPagdi%20Sambhal%20Jatta%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20at%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20meetings%20held%20at%20Lyallpur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfterwards%2C%20this%20agitation%20was%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EPagdi%20Sambhal%20Jatta%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3Emovement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELord%20Morley%2C%20Secretary%20of%20State%20for%20India%2C%20told%20the%20British%20Parliament%20that%20out%20of%20all%20the%2033%20meetings%20held%20in%20Punjab%2C%20Singh%20addressed%2019%20meetings%20as%20the%20main%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%20was%20a%20powerful%20speaker.%20One%20of%20most%20effective%20speeches%2C%20which%20he%20delivered%20on%20April%2021%20at%20Rawalpindi%2C%20was%20described%20as%20%E2%80%98highly%20seditious%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20British%20officials%2C%20and%20a%20case%20under%20Section%20124-A%20of%20sedition%20was%20registered%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%201907%2C%20the%20three%20laws%20were%20cancelled.%20However%2C%20Lala%20Lajpat%20Rai%2C%20who%20was%20also%20a%20speaker%20at%20a%20few%20of%20these%20meetings%2C%20was%20arrested%20on%20May%209%2C%20along%20with%20Singh%2C%20who%20was%20arrested%20on%20June%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20of%20them%20were%20deported%20to%20the%20Mandalay%20prison%20in%20Burma%20for%20six%20months%20under%20regulation-III%20of%201818.%20They%20were%20released%20on%20November%2011%2C%201907.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20was%20Ajit%20Singh%2C%20the%20main%20organiser%20and%20hero%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EPagdi%20Sambhal%20Jatta%3C%2Fem%3E%20movement%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAjit%20Singh%2C%20who%20was%20the%20uncle%20of%20Bhagat%20Singh%2C%20was%20born%20on%20February%2023%2C%201881%2C%20at%20Khatkar%20Kalan%20village%20in%20then%20Jalandhar%20district%20of%20pre-partition%20Punjab.%20This%20was%20the%20month%20and%20year%20when%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Tribune%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20came%20into%20existence%20in%20Lahore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20brothers%20%E2%80%93%20Arjan%20Singh%2C%20the%20father%20of%20Kishan%20Singh%20(who%20was%20the%20father%20of%20Bhagat%20Singh)%2C%20Ajit%20Singh%2C%20and%20Swarn%20Singh%20%E2%80%93%20were%20staunch%20nationalists.%20Surjan%20Singh%2C%20an%20uncle%2C%20was%20known%20to%20be%20a%20British%20supporter%2C%20which%20provoked%20sharp%20reactions%20from%20Ajit%20Singh.%20All%20three%20brothers%20graduated%20from%20Sain%20Das%20Anglo%20Sanskrit%20School%20in%20Jalandhar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20Ajit%20Singh%20pursued%20his%20law%20education%20from%20Bareilly%20college.%20During%20his%20college%20days%20in%20Bareilly%2C%20in%201903%2C%20Ajit%20Singh%2C%20with%20his%20elder%20brother%20Kishan%20Singh%2C%20had%20gone%20to%20Delhi%20to%20meet%20Indian%20princes%2C%20attending%20Delhi%20Durbar%20called%20by%20Viceroy%20Lord%20Curzon.%20They%20tried%20to%20impress%20upon%20princes%20to%20fight%20against%20British%20rulers.%20As%20per%20Ajit%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20autobiography%2C%20%3Cem%3EBuried%20Alive%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20they%20were%20in%20close%20touch%20with%20Motilal%20Ghosh%2C%20proprietor%20of%20%3Cem%3EAmrit%20Bazar%20Patrika%3C%2Fem%3E%20from%20Calcutta%20and%20Kali%20Purson%20Chatterjee%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Tribune%20%3C%2Fem%3Eat%20that%20time%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%20In%201903%2C%20Ajit%20Singh%20was%20married%20to%20Harnam%20Kaur%2C%20adopted%20daughter%20of%20Dhanpat%20Rai%20of%20Kasur%20of%20Sufi%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20Ajit%20Singh%20pursued%20his%20legal%20education%20at%20Bareilly%20College.%20During%20his%20college%20days%20in%20Bareilly%2C%20in%201903%2C%20Ajit%20Singh%2C%20along%20with%20his%20elder%20brother%20Kishan%20Singh%2C%20traveled%20to%20Delhi%20to%20meet%20Indian%20princes%20attending%20the%20Delhi%20Durbar%20called%20by%20Viceroy%20Lord%20Curzon.%20They%20attempted%20to%20persuade%20the%20princes%20to%20fight%20against%20British%20rulers.%20According%20to%20Ajit%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20autobiography%2C%20%3Cem%3EBuried%20Alive%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20they%20were%20in%20touch%20with%20Motilal%20Ghosh%2C%20the%20proprietor%20of%20%3Cem%3EAmrit%20Bazar%20Patrika%3C%2Fem%3E%20from%20Calcutta%2C%20and%20Kali%20Purson%20Chatterjee%2C%20the%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Tribune%3C%2Fem%3E%20at%20that%20time.%20In%201903%2C%20Ajit%20Singh%20married%20Harnam%20Kaur%2C%20the%20adopted%20daughter%20of%20Dhanpat%20Rai%20of%20Kasur%2C%20who%20followed%20the%20Sufi%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20beginning%20of%20revolutionary%20activities%20of%20Ajit%20Singh.%20Both%20brothers%20attended%20the%201906%20Congress%20session%20at%20Calcutta%2C%20which%20was%20presided%20over%20by%20Dada%20Bhai%20Naroji.%20They%20sided%20with%20Bal%20Gangadhar%20Tilak%20in%20Congress.%20While%20returning%20to%20Punjab%2C%20they%20formed%20the%20Bharat%20Mata%20society%2C%20which%20was%20called%20%3Cem%3EAnjuman-i-Mohabban-e-Watan%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Urdu.%20The%20society%20published%20several%20anti-British%20pamphlets%20in%20Urdu.%20Other%20members%20of%20the%20society%20were%20Sufi%20Amba%20Prasad%2C%20Ghasita%20Ram%2C%20poet%20Lal%20Chand%20Falak%2C%20Nand%20Kishore%20Mehta%2C%20Lala%20Ramsaran%20Dass%2C%20Dhanpat%20Rai%2C%20Pindi%20Das%2C%20Jaswant%20Rai%2C%20Zia%20Ullah%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhagat%20Singh%20was%20born%20on%20September%2028%2C%201907.%20In%20December%201907%2C%20Ajit%20Singh%20and%20Sufi%20Amba%20Prasad%20attended%20the%20Congress%20session%20at%20Surat%2C%20where%20B.G.%20Tilak%20presented%20Ajit%20Singh%20with%20a%20%E2%80%9CTaj-Crown%20as%20king%20of%20Panjab%20peasantry%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Ajit%20Singh%20could%20be%20arrested%20in%20some%20false%20case%2C%20he%20along%20with%20Sufi%20Ambaprasad%20left%20for%20Iran%20from%20Karachi%20by%20ship.%20He%20took%20the%20name%20Mirza%20Hassan%20Khan.%20Till%201914%2C%20he%20stayed%20in%20Iran%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Paris%2C%20and%20Switzerland.%20He%20even%20reached%20Brazil%2C%20where%20he%20spent%2018%20years%20of%20his%20life%20from%201914%20to%201932.%20From%201932%20to%201938%2C%20he%20remained%20in%20Europe%2C%20mostly%20in%20Switzerland.%20He%20taught%20Oriental%20languages%20to%20foreigners%20for%20a%20living.%20He%20could%20speak%20around%2040%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20family%20received%20the%20first%20news%20of%20him%20in%201912%20and%20then%20not%20again%20until%201928%2C%20when%20Agnes%20Smedley%2C%20an%20American%20sympathiser%20of%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20revolutionaries%2C%20wrote%20to%20B.S.%20Sandhu%20(Bhagat%20Singh)%20on%20March%2017%2C%201928%2C%20care%20of%20A.C.%20Bali%20in%20Lahore%2C%20informing%20him%20of%20Ajit%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20address%20in%20Rio%20de%20Janeiro.%20A.C.%20Bali%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20Bhagat%20Singh%20movement%20in%20Lahore%2C%20later%20became%20a%20senior%20journalist%20at%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Tribune%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20described%20this%20incident%20in%20his%20article%20on%20Ajit%20Singh%20in%20a%20collection.%20According%20to%20Bali%2C%20Bhagat%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20last%20wish%20before%20being%20executed%20was%20that%20his%20uncle%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20die%20in%20a%20foreign%20country.%20Bhagat%20Singh%20had%20been%20trying%20to%20ascertain%20his%20uncle%E2%80%99s%20whereabouts%20through%20his%20friends%2C%20especially%20Amar%20Chand%2C%20who%20had%20gone%20to%20the%20US%20for%20higher%20studies.%20Ajit%20Singh%20also%20attempted%20to%20help%20Bhagat%20Singh%20leave%20India%20to%20save%20him%20from%20the%20gallows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20long%20and%20torturous%20story%20of%20Ajit%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20life%20in%20exile.%20In%20Italy%2C%20he%20even%20created%20the%20Azad%20Hind%20Lashkar%20with%2011%2C000%20army%20men%20and%20met%20Netaji%20Subhas%20Chandra%20Bose.%20In%20Switzerland%2C%20he%20met%20Lala%20Hardyal%20and%20Champak%20Raman%20Pillai%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Lenin%2C%20Trotsky%2C%20and%20Mussolini.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20due%20to%20the%20intervention%20of%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20who%20had%20become%20the%20interim%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20India%2C%20Ajit%20Singh%20was%20released%20from%20a%20prison%20in%20Germany.%20He%20returned%20to%20India%20via%20London%20on%20March%207%2C%201947%2C%20spending%20two%20months%20in%20London%20with%20Indian%20nationalists%20to%20recuperate%20from%20ill%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Delhi%2C%20he%20was%20a%20guest%20of%20Pandit%20Nehru.%20After%20returning%20to%20Lahore%20on%20April%209%2C%20he%20received%20a%20tumultuous%20welcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20recuperate%20further%2C%20he%20went%20to%20Dalhousie%20in%20July%201947%2C%20intending%20to%20return%20by%20September.%20However%2C%20on%20the%20midnight%20of%20August%2014-15%2C%201947%2C%20after%20listening%20to%20Pandit%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Tryst%20with%20Destiny%E2%80%99%20speech%2C%20he%20felt%20overwhelmed%20and%2C%20by%20saying%20%E2%80%98Jai%20Hind%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20breathed%20his%20last%20at%20about%203%3A30%20a.m.%20in%20free%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20memorial%20at%20Panjpola%20in%20Dalhousie%20is%20now%20a%20place%20for%20paying%20tribute%20to%20the%20great%20revolutionary%20freedom%20fighter%20and%20leader%20of%20the%20Indian%20farmers%E2%80%99%20struggle%20for%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EChaman%20Lal%20is%20a%20retired%20JNU%20professor%20and%20an%20honorary%20advisor%20at%20Bhagat%20Singh%20Archives%20and%20Resource%20Centre%2C%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708699505000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F14145905%2FUnknown.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Flegacy-of-sardar-ajit-singh-remembering-the-1907-pagdi-sambhal-jatta-movement%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sardar%20Ajit%20Singh%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20movement%2C%20was%20remembered%20as%20an%20icon%20and%20a%20powerful%20inspiration%20for%20the%20farmers'%20movement%20in%20the%20Delhi%20borders%20and%20all%20over%20India.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Flegacy-of-sardar-ajit-singh-remembering-the-1907-pagdi-sambhal-jatta-movement%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22FinMin%20asks%20depts%20to%20surrender%20unspent%20Budgetary%20allocation%20by%20March%208%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708699306000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2021-06%2F15%2Ffull%2F1623766315-375.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Ffinmin-asks-depts-to-surrender-unspent-budgetary-allocation-by-march-8-124022300954_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20requested%20that%20the%20details%20of%20surrender%20of%20savings%20under%20each%20unit%20of%20appropriation%20may%20be%20sent%20to%20the%20Budget%20Division%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%20by%20the%20said%20date%20in%20a%20specified%20format%2C%20it%20said%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busin